        <!-- ~Autoret -->
        <section id="authors">
            <div class="slide-controls">
                <button id="prevBtn0" onclick="prev()">&lt;</button>
                <h2 class="section_title">AUTHORS</h2>
                <button id="nextBtn0" onclick="next()">&gt;</button>
            </div>
        <div class="card-slider">
            <div class="card-container">
                <div class="card">
                    <img src="foto/stephenking.jpg">
                    <div class="card-info">
                        <h3>Stephen King</h3>
                        <p>Stephen Edwin King is an American author. Called the "King of Horror",he has also explored other genres,like suspense,science-fiction, and mystery.He has written approximately 200 short stories,most of which have been published in collections.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
    
                <div class="card">
                    <img src="foto/edgatallanpoe.jpg">
                    <div class="card-info">
                        <h3>Edgar Allan Poe</h3>
                        <p>Edgar Allan Poe was an American writer, poet, author, editor, and literary critic who is best known for his poetry and short stories, particularly his tales of mystery and the macabre. He is widely regarded as a central figure of Gothic fiction in the United States.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
       
                <div class="card">
                    <img src="foto/richardprice.jpg">
                    <div class="card-info">
                        <h3>Richard Price</h3>
                        <p>Richard Price is an American novelist,known for the books The Wanderers, Clockers and Lush Life. Price's novels explore late-20th-century urban America in a gritty, realistic manner that has brought him considerable literary acclaim.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
       
                <div class="card">
                    <img src="foto/ShirleyJack.jpg">
                    <div class="card-info">
                        <h3>Shirley Jackson</h3>
                        <p>Shirley Hardie Jackson was an American writer known primarily for her works of horror and mystery. Her writing career spanned over two decades, during which she composed six novels, two memoirs, and more than approximately 200 short stories.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
       
                <div class="card">
                    <img src="foto/neil.jpg">
                    <div class="card-info">
                        <h3>Neil Gaiman</h3>
                        <p>Neil Richard MacKinnon Gaiman is an English author of short fiction, novels, comic books, graphic novels, audio theatre, and screenplays. His works include the comic book series The Sandman and the novels Good Omens, Stardust, Coraline.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
    
                <div class="card">
                    <img src="foto/lovecraft.jpg">
                    <div class="card-info">
                        <h3>H.P.Lovecraft</h3>
                        <p>Howard Phillips Lovecraft was an American author from Rhode Island of horror,fantasy and science fiction.Lovecraft's major inspiration and invention was cosmic horror: life is incomprehensible to human minds and the universe is fundamentally alien. </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
    
                <div class="card">
                    <img src="foto/algernon.jpg">
                    <div class="card-info">
                        <h3>Algernon Blackwood</h3>
                        <p>Algernon Henry Blackwood was an English broadcasting narrator, journalist, novelist , and among the most prolific ghost story writers in the history of the genre.His two best-known stories are probably "The Willows" and "The Wendigo". </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
    
                <div class="card">
                    <img src="foto/moore.jpg">
                    <div class="card-info">
                        <h3>Alan Moore</h3>
                        <p>Alan Moore is an English author known for his work in comic books including Watchmen, V for Vendetta, The Ballad of Halo Jones,Batman: The Killing Joke.He is widely recognised as one of the best comic book writers in the English language.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

